page.title: 16Henham's nearest vet.
page.content: The rarest animal Mr.Mckeating has ever had to cure was a vitamesse pot bellied pig,and the most common one is a dog.Mr.Mckeating has 80 animals a day to heal,at average.There is a computer at the surgery where he keeps animals health and information,and he uses it about 40 times a day.Mr.Mckeating also has to put animals down by anaethetics or with a large gun.The rarest animal he has ever had to put down is a buzzard and the most common animal is a dog.The letters after Mr.Mckeatings name BVMS stand for Batchelor of Veterinary Medicine and Surgery.The hardest animal to train is a pig and the easiest is a lamb.The most animals Mr.Mckeating has ever had in one day is 450 cows and the least is 20 animals a day.
